  "notes": [
    "All transfer applicants must meet the University of California admissions eligibility requirements and the campus’s admission selection criteria. All requirements must be completed by the end of the spring term prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility and admission to UC Santa Cruz, visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that guarantees your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
    "THIS IS A SCREENING MAJOR. Screening majors require completion of specific preparatory coursework and/or a minimum GPA. For details on the specific screening requirements for this major, refer to the \" Transfer Admission Screening Policy \" below. Additional coursework listed under \"Recommended Preparation\" is not required for admission but is strongly recommended to support timely degree completion. For more information, including a list of screening majors and non-screening majors , visit the UCSC Admissions website.",
    "Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level (IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the Degree Progress Unit website .",
    "Art & Design: Games + Playable Media B.A. Transfer Admission Screening Policy Transfer students must complete the following three courses, or their articulated equivalents, with a grade of C (2.0) or better in each course by the end of the spring term prior to transferring in the fall: ONE Intro to 2D Concepts course (section A below) ONE Intro to 3D Concepts course (section B below) ONE Art and Design Topics course (section C below) Refer to the \"Required Major Preparation Courses\" section below for lists of courses approved to fulfill these requirements. Strongly Recommended Major Preparation In addition to the required courses listed above, prospective transfer students are strongly advised to complete the California General Education Transfer Curriculum (Cal-GETC) or all UC Santa Cruz general education requirements before transferring. Transfer students who meet the screening criteria outlined above and fulfill the general education requirements can complete the major within two years after transfer to UC Santa Cruz, as detailed in the Academic Planner section under the \"Requirements and Planners\" tab in the UC Santa Cruz General Catalog . For guidance on incorporating Cal-GETC into your academic plan, consult your community college counselor. Please visit the Performance, Play & Design website to learn more about this major. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Art & Design: Games + Playable Media B.A. Program Statement"
